      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BEN LIKES SCOTCH (2) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at this track over 400m behind Ribery (23.19) in a Grade 6/MDN. Placed at his previous run. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Should be very hard to beat this time. SEBON KNIGHT (7) has been in the frame at his last two runs, most recently when second (23.00) in a Grade 6 over 400m at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw. Can find the frame this time. BOUNDING HOME (4) produced a moderate performance last time when fifth at this track over 400m behind Zipping Wichita (23.20) in a Grade 6. Was in the money prior to that. Has ability and can measure up. LIFE OF RILEY (1) is building a nice sequence of placings – hard to fault that form.",
